id: pm-ne67
title: Add --compact mode to pm activity for agent-friendly condensed output
description: "pm activity output embeds full JSON-patch arrays per operation, making it very verbose. Agents scanning for recent changes have to parse ~100-line patch blocks. A --compact mode showing only op, id, ts, author per entry would reduce output by ~90% for common audit workflows."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: activity,agents,output,ux
created_at: "2026-05-01T18:59:32.119Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-01T19:28:54.131Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-3fti
resolution: Added --compact flag to activity command producing condensed id/op/ts/author/msg entries
expected_result: pm activity --compact returns ~90% smaller output with only essential audit fields
actual_result: compact_activity array emitted with id/op/ts/author/msg only; streaming mode supports compact; full activity array empty in compact mode
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-01T19:21:17.943Z",cursor-agent,"Feature implemented: --compact flag on pm activity strips patch/before_hash/after_hash, returns compact_activity array with only id, op, ts, author, msg. Non-compact mode unchanged. Streaming mode supports compact entries. End-to-end verified: pm activity --compact --limit 5 --json returns condensed entries. Tests: 16/16 history-activity-command.spec.ts passed. Build: clean."
